title: NDFD, NOAA, Significant Wave Height in GOM coastal waters, USA, July 8, 2010
name: NDFD, NOAA, Significant Wave Height in GOM coastal waters, USA, July 8, 2010
description:
The poly shapefile shows significant wave height data for portions of coastal waters in the GOM.
The data was extracted from NDFD's extraction program and then converted to shapefile. The NDFD wave height predictions are valid between 7 to 18 Hrs UTC. 

Note that compared to July 7, the seas are much calmer in the vicinity of Deep Water Horizon and the significant wave activity has shifted westward towards Texas coastal waters. 
Look elsewhere on Finder! for wave data over the next several days. Use key word "Wave height".
